1
Key Responsibilities 

• Design, develop, test, and deploy smart contracts for blockchain-based payment and asset systems.
• Build and maintain integrations between blockchain networks and centralized backend services.
• Implement secure wallet, key management, and transaction-signing mechanisms.
• Develop APIs and services that enable on-chain and off-chain interactions.
• Ensure security, scalability, and reliability of blockchain and crypto components.
• Conduct code reviews, testing, and support smart contract audits and remediation.
• Collaborate with product, backend, compliance, and infrastructure teams.
• Monitor live blockchain systems, troubleshoot issues, and optimize performance.


Skills and Experience 

• Proven experience as a Blockchain or Crypto Developer in production environments.
• Strong experience with Ethereum / EVM-based blockchains.
• Advanced proficiency in Solidity and smart contract development.
• Experience with blockchain development frameworks (Hardhat, Truffle, Foundry, or similar).
• Backend development experience using Node.js (JavaScript/TypeScript), Go, or Python.
• Solid understanding of cryptography, digital signatures, and blockchain security principles.
• Experience integrating Web3 libraries (Ethers.js, Web3.js) and RPC providers.
• Knowledge of REST APIs, microservices, and distributed systems.
• Experience with cloud infrastructure, CI/CD pipelines, and containerization (Docker).


Nice to Have 

• Experience with non-EVM chains (Solana, Polkadot, Cosmos, or similar).
• Experience in fintech, payments, or financial services environments.
• Knowledge of Layer-2 scaling solutions and cross-chain protocols.
• Experience with blockchain security audits or formal verification.
• Understanding of AML/KYC and regulatory considerations for crypto systems.
• Experience with tokenomics, stablecoins, or programmable payments.
• Prior startup or high-growth technology environment experience.
