3
Governance & Compliance
Enforce IAM governance frameworks, policies, standards, and procedures. Support periodic access reviews, ISO compliance activities, and audit requests. Maintain accurate documentation for onboarding, offboarding, and access certification processes. Identify gaps in control execution and recommend improvements.
 Ticketing & Operational Support
Process and resolve IAM-related tickets, including access provisioning, deprovisioning, role changes, and account issues. Perform timely escalation of complex access requests to appropriate teams. Maintain SLA compliance and provide high-quality support to business users. Document repeatable procedures and contribute to knowledge-base updates.
 Role & Access Management
Assist with reviewing role-based access models (RBAC) and access groups. Validate access requests to ensure least privilege and segregation of duties (SoD).Work with application owners to understand access patterns and governance requirements.
 Security & Risk Management
Identify and report potential access risks and policy violations. Support incident investigations related to identity or access breaches. Partner with Security Engineering to ensure IAM tooling and processes align with evolving threats.
 Continuous Improvement
Identify opportunities to automate or streamline ticketing and governance workflows. Participate in IAM projects, system upgrades, and process optimization initiatives. Provide input for improving audit readiness and reducing manual workloads.
